def: Legally required to be returned, delivered, given, or rendered;as, a writ or precept returnable at a certain day; a verdictreturnable to the court.
Covered with induvi√¶, as the upper part of the trunk of a palmtree.
One who holds up a train, as of a robe.
One of the Hemiptera; an hemipter.
Pertaining to, or designating, the phenol formerly calledoxyphenic acid, and now oxyphenol and pyrocatechin. See Pyrocatechin.

Like a slut; untidy; indecently negligent of cleanliness;disorderly; as, a sluttish woman.Why is thy lord so slutish, I thee pray. Chaucer.An air of liberal, though sluttish, plenty, indicated the wealthyfarmer. Sir W. Scott.-- Slut"tish*ly, adv.-- Slut"tish*ness, n.
Feeding on plants or herbage; phytophagous; as, phytivorousanimals. Ray.
One who, or that which, aids.
Pertaining to the time of equal day and night; -- applied tothe equinoctial line. Whewell.
A player at dice; a dice player; a gamester.As false as dicers' oaths. Shak.
Resembling a fan; -- specifically (Bot.), folded up like a fan,as certain leaves; plicate.
